      "data": {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "type": "prose",
            "text": "SO1 characterizes the accuracy, robustness, and privacy of the biometric subsystem. DID lookup resolves credential state first; biometric processing executes only on active credentials. The results below validate five dimensions: face recognition accuracy under backbone upgrade, environmental robustness, fingerprint quality stratification, hierarchical fusion effectiveness, and cancelable template unlinkability."
          },
          {
            "type": "prose",
            "text": "Two paired comparisons isolate the effect of replacing InceptionResNet-v1 with EfficientNet-B0 as the embedding backbone, evaluated on (a) YouTube Faces Database (YTFDB) and (b) a local kiosk dataset. The table below reports Equal Error Rate (EER), the cancelable-domain False Match Rate at the EER threshold, and the ISO 30136 D_sys unlinkability metric for each condition."
          },
          {
            "type": "table",
            "caption": "Face Recognition Performance",
            "headers": [
              "Condition",
              "Backbone",
              "Dataset",
              "EER (%)",
              "FMR @ EER (%)",
              "D_sys",
              "Unlinkability"
            ],
            "rows": [
              [
                "C1",
                "InceptionResNet",
                "YTFDB",
                "14.52",
                "2.10",
                "0.1694",
                "Linkable"
              ],
              [
                "C2",
                "EfficientNet",
                "YTFDB",
                "15.40",
                "0.19",
                "0.1960",
                "Linkable"
              ],
              [
