                "Unlinkable"
              ]
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "prose",
            "text": "EfficientNet-B0 on local data reduced EER by 16.99 percentage points (26.32% → 9.33%). On YTFDB, a marginal raw EER trade-off (+0.88 pp) was accepted to compress cancelable FMR from 2.10% → 0.19%. Raw EER is operationally irrelevant since the system never uses raw embeddings, only cancelable templates."
          },
          {
            "type": "prose",
            "text": "Both the Wilcoxon signed-rank test and the paired t-test confirm that the backbone switch produced statistically significant distributional shifts on both datasets (all p < 0.0001). Cohen's d indicates a medium effect on YTFDB (d = −0.66) and a small effect on the local dataset (d = −0.49). The effect is smaller locally because EfficientNet-B0 produces tighter, more concentrated score distributions; the improvement shows up as a dramatic EER compression rather than a large distributional shift."
          },
          {
            "type": "table",
            "caption": "Backbone Architecture Effect (Statistical Tests)",
            "headers": [
              "Statistic",
              "YTFDB",
              "Local"
            ],
            "rows": [
              [
                "N (paired)",
                "5,000",
                "5,000"
              ],
              [
                "Wilcoxon W",
                "2,335,832",
                "3,895,071"
              ],
              [
                "Wilcoxon p-value",
                "0.0000",
                "1.5717 × 10⁻¹¹⁷"
              ],
              [
