          },
          {
            "type": "prose",
            "text": "Despite a statistically significant distributional shift in embedding distance (Cohen's d = 1.42, a large effect), FNMR remained exactly 0.00% in both conditions, meaning no genuine user was rejected regardless of environmental variation. The system's verification threshold is set conservatively enough that even the worst-case uncontrolled embedding distances fall well within the acceptance region."
          },
          {
            "type": "prose",
            "text": "Fingerprint fuzzy extraction (Sample-Then-Lock) was characterized in isolation over 2,500 trials (50 mated, 2,450 impostor). The best-performing configuration was L=1024, k=8, yielding a calibrated EER of 7.97% at V_ratio = 0.0896."
          },
          {
            "type": "table",
            "caption": "Security Performance of Fingerprint Gate",
            "headers": [
              "Metric",
              "Result (%)",
              "Trials",
              "95% CI"
            ],
            "rows": [
              [
                "FMR",
                "10.53",
                "258 / 2,450",
                "[9.34%, 11.81%]"
              ],
              [
                "FNMR",
                "32.00",
                "16 / 50",
                "[19.52%, 46.70%]"
              ]
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "prose",
            "text": "Quality stratification was tested by correlating V_ratio with Jensen-Shannon Divergence across 18 configurations. Spearman ρ = −0.53 (p = 0.139), a moderate negative correlation that fell below the pre-registered threshold (ρ > 0.7, p < 0.05). This is the single unsatisfied statistical claim in the study, attributable to an underpowered design (9 discrete configuration points, narrow JSD range 0.458–0.500). However, practical validation is clear: the high-quality configuration (L=2048, k=4) achieved EER 2.34% versus the low-quality configuration (L=1024, k=4) at EER 8.69%, a 3.72× error reduction."
          },
