          {
            "type": "prose",
            "text": "The hierarchical fusion gate (fingerprint first, then face) was evaluated over 2,500 trials using calibrated thresholds. The fingerprint gate blocked all 2,450 impostors before face comparison even executed, reducing the adjusted system-level FMR to exactly 0.00%. Cross-domain independence between fingerprint and face scores was confirmed via Mann–Whitney U (U=610,937, p=5.19×10⁻¹², d=−0.36), ruling out correlated vulnerabilities."
          },
          {
            "type": "table",
            "caption": "Hierarchical Security Performance",
