          },
          {
            "type": "prose",
            "text": "Cancelable template unlinkability was quantified via the ISO/IEC 30136 D_sys metric across all four backbone conditions. The threshold for unlinkability is D_sys < 0.1. Production models (C3 and C4, trained on local data) satisfy this requirement, with C3 achieving near-perfect unlinkability at D_sys = 0.0042. YTFDB-trained models (C1, C2) fail the threshold, confirming that domain-specific fine-tuning is essential for both accuracy and privacy. Unlinkability prevents cross-credential identity inference after DID revocation, eliminating that attack vector."
          },
